{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, Wang et al. [123] model social cluster formation as a cooperative game, where agents collaboratively optimize group strategies to enhance overall utility while ensuring equitable coalition benefit allocation.",
    "From a joint behavioral and gametheoretic perspective, Lalmohammed [132] develops a welfare modeling framework for human-AI economic ecosystems, incorporating trust evolution, risk aversion, and collaboration synergies.",
    "Using agent-based modeling, the study shows that dynamic trust-building and equitable incentive distribution are pivotal for maximizing collective welfare in mixed human-AI systems.",
    "• Reputation mechanisms track agents' historical performance, prioritizing high-reputation agents for critical tasks and discouraging malicious behavior.",
    "For instance, Xu et al. [128] propose a hierarchical reputation framework that selects reliable agents based on reputation scores for secure collaboration in dynamic and uncertain environments."
  ]
}